div.p:
Concerning the Apparitions of Chriſt after his reſurrection, the Scripture records that our Sauiour was on earth forty daies, and in that time appeared to many at ſeuerall times, ſhewing himſelfe aliue from the dead, and giuing order concerning his Kingdome: as hee was forty daies in giuing the Law to Moſes on the Mount, ſo was he forty daies in giuing order about the new Law to the Apoſtles, and hee that began to conſecrate himſelfe to the office appointed him by his Father in faſting forty daies, doth now take forty daies, both to lay downe that office, and to conſecrate the Miniſtery of his Diſciples. Now concerning theſe Apparitions diuers things are to be conſidered;


1. The Reaſons why he appeared.

2. The Perſons to whom he appeared.
